In a temporary browser console or a short test script, import supabase from src/lib/supabase.js and call:

  const { data, error } = await supabase.from('profiles').select('id').limit(1);
  console.log(data, error);

Expected: data is [] and error is null (empty table, RLS blocks anon without a session — which is correct). If error.code is 'PGRST301' (RLS violation without auth), that confirms RLS is working. A null error with empty data also confirms connectivity. Remove the test script before committing.
